Package com.aitusoftware.babl.websocket

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BackPressureStrategy
    Strategy to employ when the session container cannot send data to a Session.
    ClientEventHandler
    Event handler for web-socket client events.
    ConnectionValidator
    Used to perform validation on a new connection.
    Constants
    Constant values relating to the web-socket protocol.
    SendResult
    Indicates the result of attempting to send data to an endpoint.
    Session
    Interface for interacting with a web-socket session.
    ValidationResultPublisher
    Publisher for validation results.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AlwaysValidConnectionValidator
    ConnectionValidator that will always succeed.
    BablServer
    Main class for starting a web socket server.
    Client
    Allocation-free web-socket client used for testing purposes.
    DisconnectBackPressureStrategy
    Strategy that will close the web-socket session when back-pressure occurs.
    DropMessageBackPressureStrategy
    Strategy that will drop a message when back-pressure occurs.
    MaintainBackPressureStrategy
    Strategy that will propagate back-pressure when back-pressure occurs.
    SessionContainers
    A container for the server and any dependencies.
    ValidationResult
    A container to describing the result of validation for a given session.
    WebSocketSession
    Models a web socket session; used by an Application to send messages to a peer.
  • Enum Summary

    Reason for session disconnection.
